{
  "document_id": "job-4",
  "title": "Job 4",
  "type": "scripture",
  "translation": "NRSVue",
  "blocks": [
    {
      "block_id": "job-4-heading-eliphaz-speaks:-job-",
      "type": "heading",
      "text": "Eliphaz Speaks: Job Has Sinned"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-4-1",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 1,
      "text": "Then Eliphaz the Temanite answered:"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-4-2",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 2,
      "text": "“If one ventures a word with you, will you be offended?"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-4-3",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 3,
      "text": "See, you have instructed many;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-4-4",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 4,
      "text": "Your words have supported those who were stumbling,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-4-5",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 5,
      "text": "But now it has come to you, and you are impatient;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-4-6",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 6,
      "text": "Is not your fear of God your confidence"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-4-7",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 7,
      "text": "“Think now, who that was innocent ever perished?"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-4-8",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 8,
      "text": "As I have seen, those who plow iniquity"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-4-9",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 9,
      "text": "By the breath of God they perish,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-4-10",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 10,
      "text": "The roar of the lion, the voice of the fierce lion,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-4-11",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 11,
      "text": "The strong lion perishes for lack of prey,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-4-12",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 12,
      "text": "“Now a word came stealing to me;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-4-13",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 13,
      "text": "Amid thoughts from visions of the night,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-4-14",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 14,
      "text": "dread came upon me and trembling,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-4-15",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 15,
      "text": "A spirit glided past my face;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-4-16",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 16,
      "text": "It stood still,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-4-17",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 17,
      "text": "‘Can mortals be righteous before God?"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-4-18",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 18,
      "text": "Even in his servants he puts no trust,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-4-19",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 19,
      "text": "how much more those who live in houses of clay,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-4-20",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 20,
      "text": "Between morning and evening they are destroyed;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-4-21",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 21,
      "text": "Their tent cord is plucked up within them,"
    }
  ]
}